The Administrator of the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services, Seema Verma, argues that healthcare should embrace consumerism and empower patients to make informed decisions about their care. She cites studies that show providing price transparency tools to patients can lower costs without compromising quality. Verma believes that transparency around price and quality is essential for driving value-based transformation in the healthcare system. She also highlights the need for greater price transparency in the industry and emphasizes the importance of patients owning and controlling their health records. Verma concludes by stating that the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services are committed to putting patients first and transforming the healthcare system to empower patients with the information they need.